entry.title: Alternanthera denticulata s.l., Alternanthera denticulata s.s.
Oxalis exilis
entry.content: Hairs on lowest branches (not stems leading to leaves or flowers) are mostly antrorse/appressed (ie. forwards/upwards against stem) - this is true for O.exilis and O.perennans.

entry.title: Arthropodium sp. 3 (aff. strictum)
entry.content: Suspect this is A. sp. 3. Anthers lack yellow appendages and I can see at least one node with two flowers.

entry.title: Geranium sp. 3
entry.content: Three pics showing 1) flower and spring-summer leaf, 2) close-up of spring-summer leaf with narrow lobes, 3) close-up of over-wintering leaf with broad lobes. In Spring, both leaf-types are seen.

entry.title: Pellaea falcata s.l., Pellaea falcata s.s.
Convolvulus angustissimus subsp. omnigracilis
entry.content: Fruiting pedicel is distictly recurved, which rules out C. remotus. 2nd pic indicates possibly subsp. angustissimus with its broad lower cauline leaves but the higher leaves mean it is probably omnigracilis.
